Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 14:15:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/7] Fix bugs blocking automatic paper trades end-to-end

Verified the full pipeline live (uvicorn + mock feed) and found the automatic
trade path was silently broken in three more places beyond the earlier wiring
fix:

- config/settings.yaml: market_analyst_agent was discovered by the agent
  registry but never listed under agents:, so it was never instantiated. It is
  the only producer of "candle" -> "market_analysis" events, so decision
  scoring's market_analysis component was always 0/missing.
- scoring/engine.py: RiskEngine.get_dashboard_metrics() reports system health
  as OPERATIONAL/RESTRICTED, but the confidence calculator and ChiefDecisionAgent
  expect the ALLOW/BLOCK/REDUCE_POSITION vocabulary RiskEngine.validate_order()
  uses. The mismatch meant the risk component of every decision score was always
  read as blocked, capping confidence and forcing every decision into BLOCKED.
- scoring/models.py + scoring/engine.py: DecisionScoreResult never carried a
  risk_status or recommended_strategy field, even though ChiefDecisionAgent's
  ConflictResolver and ApprovalManager both read score_data["risk_status"] to
  gate approval. The field was always absent, so both always fell back to their
  (different, both wrong) hardcoded defaults. Added the field and populated it
  from the (now-translated) risk status computed in evaluate_decision().

With these fixes the live pipeline now reaches Chief Decision: MANUAL_REVIEW
with "All checks passed successfully" (previously stuck at REJECTED/BLOCKED),
confirming Scanner -> Decision Score -> Chief Decision -> Risk are correctly
wired end-to-end. Full auto-approval (>=80% confidence) additionally requires
a genuinely trending regime (ADX needs 28 M1 candles to warm up), which is
expected market-data warm-up time, not a bug.

